            width: 100%;
        }
        #visualizationCanvas {
            width: 100%;
            height: 200px;
            background-color: #e9ecef;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="module">
    <div class="module-title">Introduction to Bubble Sort</div>
    <div>This module introduces the concept of Bubble Sort, a simple sorting algorithm that compares adjacent elements and swaps them if they are in the wrong order.</div>
</div>

<div class="module">
    <div class="module-title">Interactive Sorting Array</div>
    <div>The goal here is to allow users to define their own array of numbers to sort. Enter numbers in the input field and click the "Create Array" button.</div>
    <div class="interactive-area">
        <input type="text" id="arrayInput" placeholder="Enter numbers separated by commas" />
        <button class="button" onclick="createArray()">Create Array</button>
    </div>
    <div id="arrayDisplay"></div>
</div>

<div class="module">
    <div class="module-title">Visual Bubble Sort</div>
    <div>This module demonstrates the sorting process visually. Click "Start Sorting" to see how Bubble Sort works in real-time.</div>
    <div class="interactive-area">
        <button class="button" onclick="startSorting()">Start Sorting</button>
    </div>
    <div id="visualizationCanvas"></div>
</div>

<div class="module">
    <div class="module-title">Adjust Array Size</div>
    <div>Change the size of the array to see how Bubble Sort performs with larger or smaller datasets. Use the slider below.</div>
    <input type="range" min="3" max="20" value="10" class="slider" id="arraySizeSlider" oninput="updateArraySize()">
    <span id="arraySizeDisplay">10</span>
    <div id="newArrayDisplay"></div>
</div>

<script>
    let array = [];

    function createArray() {
        const input = document.getElementById('arrayInput').value;
        array = input.split(',').map(num => Number(num.trim())).filter(Number.isFinite);
        displayArray(array);
    }

    function displayArray(arr) {
        const arrayDisplay = document.getElementById('arrayDisplay');
        arrayDisplay.innerHTML = '';
        arr.forEach(num => {
            const bar = document.createElement('div');
            bar.className = 'sort-bar';
            bar.style.height = num * 10 + 'px'; // Scale height
            arrayDisplay.appendChild(bar);
        });
    }

    async function startSorting() {
        const originalArray = [...array];
        for (let i = 0; i < originalArray.length; i++) {
            for (let j = 0; j < originalArray.length - i - 1; j++) {
                if (originalArray[j] > originalArray[j + 1]) {
                    // Swap
                    [originalArray[j], originalArray[j + 1]] = [originalArray[j + 1], originalArray[j]];
                    displaySortedArray(originalArray);
                    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 500)); // Delay for visualization
                }
            }
        }
    }

    function displaySortedArray(arr) {
        const visualizationCanvas = document.getElementById('visualizationCanvas');
        visualizationCanvas.innerHTML = '';
        arr.forEach(num => {
            const bar = document.createElement('div');
            bar.className = 'sort-bar';
            bar.style.height = num * 10 + 'px';
            visualizationCanvas.appendChild(bar);
        });
    }

    function updateArraySize() {
        const size = document.getElementById('arraySizeSlider').value;
        document.getElementById('arraySizeDisplay').innerText = size;
        const newArray = Array.from({ length: size }, () => Math.floor(Math.random() * 100));
        displayArray(newArray);
        array = newArray; // Update current array
    }

    // Initial Array Display
    updateArraySize();
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

In this HTML structure, the user can interactively learn about Bubble Sort through various modules. Each module progressively builds from understanding the concept, creating an array, visualizing the sort, and adjusting the size of the array for different sorting scenarios. The design emphasizes clear separation of elements with appropriate spacing, ensuring usability on various screen sizes.
